<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="E" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Ethiop" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Ethiop,</orth> a native of Ethiopia: <bibl n="shak. pp 242" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 242</bibl> and <bibl n="shak. lll 4.3.118" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 3, 118</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.6.26" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. II, 6, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 5.4.38" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 4, 38</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.3.268" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 3, 268</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.257" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 2, 257</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.5.48" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 5, 48</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 2.2.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. II, 2, 20</bibl>. Adjectively: <cit><quote>such E. words, blacker in their effect than in their countenance,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 4.3.35" default="NO" valid="yes">As IV, 3, 35</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>